</ul>

<p>what about for DSSR?</p>
<ul>
  <li>same thing but with PHP and Databases like MySQL or PostgreSQL</li>
  <li>and Servers like Apache, <a href="https://www.wampserver.com/en/">WAMPP</a>, <a href="https://www.apachefriends.org/index.html">XAMPP</a>, or <a href="https://laragon.org/">Laragon</a></li>
  <li>MENN Stack or (MEAN Stack but i havenâ€™t used thisâ€¦ A is <a href="https://angular.io/docs">Angular</a>)</li>
</ul>

<p>what about stacks for CSR?</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://reactjs.org/">React.js</a> Framework</li>
  <li><a href="https://nodejs.org/en/">Node.js</a> and will use <a href="https://expressjs.com/">Express.js</a> Framwork</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.nginx.com/">NGINX</a> for the server and reverse proxy</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.mongodb.com/">MongoDB</a>
they usually call this MERN Stack (Mongo Express Reat Node) but you could also use MySQL or PostgreSQL on this so call it PERN Stack :-)</li>
</ul>

<p>with Microservices</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://docs.docker.com/">Docker</a>
i mainly use docker since i havenâ€™t got the time to read the <a href="https://kubernetes.io/">Kubernetes</a> Documentation but they say that itâ€™s much easier to pair docker with kubernetes since you can use kubernetes to manage docker containers afterwards</li>
